Derrick Spies, Correspondent Cape
Town – A man has died in a fatal crash on
the R102 outside Kuilsriver, when his car
ploughed through the median into oncoming traffic. Western Cape Traffic
spokesperson, Kenny Africa said the accident had occurred at around 11:15
on Saturday morning.  He said the vehicle, a Ford
Telstar, had been travelling along the R102, in the direction of Kuilsriver
before Buttskop Drive, when the driver appeared to lose control and went over
the median into oncoming traffic.  Africa said the motor vehicle had
then caught alight while the man, who was the only occupant, was still inside.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  